            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;Of course, that isn&apos;t the case here and there&apos;s no point in doing the same thing two different ways. For an integer you could get the line into a string and then use &lt;code&gt;std::stoi()&lt;/code&gt;, but then it&apos;s not so clear there&apos;s an advantage. But I tend to prefer to just use &lt;code&gt;std::getline()&lt;/code&gt; for line-oriented input and then deal with parsing the line in whatever way makes sense. I think it&apos;s less error prone.&lt;/span&gt;

